{{DISPLAYTITLE:OFIELD_KAPPA}}{{TAGDEF|OFIELD_KAPPA|[real]}}

Description: The tag {{TAG|OFIELD_KAPPA}} sets the strength of the bias potential in the [[:Category:Interface pinning|Interface pinning]] method.
----
The bias potential in the [[:Category:Interface pinning|Interface pinning]] method is written as
::<math>U_\text{bias}(\mathbf{R}) = \frac\kappa2 \left(Q_6(\mathbf{R}) - A\right)^2 </math>.
The tag {{TAG|OFIELD_KAPPA}} method sets the strength of the bias potential <math>\kappa</math>. The unit of <math>\kappa</math> is <math>\textrm{eV}/(\textrm{unit} \,\, \textrm{ of }\,\, Q)^2</math>.

